Package fr.sorbonne_u.alasca.physical_data

Utilities for physical data representation.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MeasureI<T>
    The interface MeasureI<T> mainly marks classes from which instance of physical measures or values are represented.
    TimingI
    The interface TimingI defines operation which are used to retrieve timing information associated to some entity, like the time at which some data has been retrieved or computed.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractSignalData
    The class AbstractSignalData is the common type of all signal data, be it single or composed.
    ComposedSignalData
    The class ComposedSignalData implements a composed signal data, with its own time stamping information, and combining several single or composed signal data having their own time stamping information.
    Measure<T extends java.io.Serializable>
    The class Measure implements a physical value about or measure made on some phenomenon having a value of generic type T and a MeasurementUnit.
    SignalData<T extends java.io.Serializable>
    The class SignalData implements a simple signal data, combining a measure and its time stamping information inherited from TimedEntity.
    TimedEntity
    The class TimedEntity defines the common fields and methods managing the timing information of timed entities.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    MeasurementUnit
    The enumeration MeasurementUnit defines in a simple way the measurement units used in the HEM application.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IncoherentTimestampersException
    The class IncoherentTimeReferenceException represents the exception raised when the time references of the single signal data appearing recursively in a composed signal data are not sufficiently aligned to have their time stamps comparable.
